            <h2>Movies</h2>
            <h3><strong>A More Immersive Movie Experience</strong></h3>
            <div class="container">
                <img src="assets/images/movies.png" alt="title" width="300px">
            </div>
            <h4>
                Innovative directors and producers are already using AR and VR to make the movie-watching experience more immersive.
            </h4>
            <h4>
                Directors can film 360-degree footage to help viewers feel like they are really part of the action. This is a great way to help transport people into virtual locations all over the world and let them experience what it’s like to be there in person.
            </h4>
            <h4>
                A lot of the technology that has been developed in video games is now being used in movie making, as well. In the future, directors will be able to make movies where the content is generated on the fly using AI, and you’ll be able to interact with characters and settings based on your own choices. Everyone will have a completely unique experience because the personalized movie content will be generated specifically for you.
            </h4>
            <h4>
                Many movies are also shooting behind-the-scenes footage that is available to watch in VR, so you can explore the set and see what happened as the movie was being made.
            </h4>
        </div>
    </div>


